  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) obligations\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory financial institution reporting\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Regulatory agency oversight\n- Criminal prosecution\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping\n- Risk assessment procedures\n\n6. Jurisdictional Considerations\n- Cross-border cooperation\n- Extradition agreements\n- Information sharing protocols\n\n7. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced technological surveillance\n\nThe specific details and implementation can vary between countries, but these general principles form the core of modern money laundering legal frameworks.",
